info.headline: Wind Advisory issued January 11 at 2:41AM PST until January 12 at 4:00PM PST by NWS Eureka
info.description: ...WIND ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM 8 AM THIS MORNING TO 4 PM THURSDAY... * WHAT...Southeast winds 20 to 30 mph with gusts to 60 mph expected. * WHERE...Del Norte Interior, Southwestern Humboldt, Northern Humboldt Interior, Southern Humboldt Interior, and Northwestern Mendocino Interior. * WHEN...From 8 AM Wednesday to 4 PM Thursday. * IMPACTS...Gusty winds could blow around unsecured objects. Tree limbs could be blown down and a few power outages may result. PRECAUTIONARY/PREPAREDNESS ACTIONS... Use extra caution when driving, especially if operating a high profile vehicle. Secure outdoor objects.
